<br>
Then I hear a shout, &quot;Muglwump is camped&quot;.  Hmm, I think to myself, I guess I&quot;ll let the young ones try, and if they fail, or get in trouble, I will have another shot.  (He's quite a challenge to me by myself, as well!)<br>
<br>
So I reply to them (as one approached me) along the lines of &quot;I will wait.&quot;<br>
<br>
As I stand there (don't try to sit in the warrens, it's not good for your health!) I see someone running past me and engage Muglwump.  &quot;Hmm&quot; I think to myself. &quot;I guess they were just about ready to engage and just did it a bit early, fearing for me to attack him first?&quot; ... then one of the ladies gives me quite a rude gesture.<br>
<br>
&quot;Huh?&quot;<br>
<br>
And she says to me... &quot;Honor my ass&quot; ... again I'm confused.  <br>
<br>
Alas, I take a look at the warrior that had engaged Muglwump.. he's fighting by himself, and he looks like he could take me quite easily.   That's when it clicks.. the warrior just took Muglwump, ignoring the other folks standing there right in front.  I send a quick message to the warrior saying &quot;Uhm.. didn't you see everyone here?&quot; and he was rather condescending... but what can I do, tis not my doing.<br>
<br>
Alas, try to explain that to the other group... the one lady was quite angry at having her work undone, and it was quite a trial to explain to her that it wasn't my doing.  Eventually one of the other folks in her group calmed her down.. as I was pondering about having the reputation of my guild endangered.  I do try to be honorable in my actions, as my guild, the League of Honour, is quite wont to do.  With a little pushing and nudging, the lady apologized. I just wish the warrior had had a sense of honor in him... <br>
<br>
<br>
The moral of the story?  Keep in mind that even if you are angry.. please take it out on the RIGHT person.<br>
<br>
Thank you,<br>
Kyrial Moonlight<br>
